3
00:01:33,130 --> 00:01:37,110
[MUSIC PLAYING]

4
00:01:48,070 --> 00:01:49,560
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

5
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:51,550
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

6
00:01:51,550 --> 00:01:53,050
Hey.

7
00:01:53,050 --> 00:01:55,540
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

8
00:01:55,540 --> 00:01:59,610
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

9
00:02:01,570 --> 00:02:05,040
[CHATTER]

10
00:02:22,930 --> 00:02:27,900
[HOWLING]

11
00:03:14,130 --> 00:03:18,600
[MUSIC PLAYING]

12
00:03:40,070 --> 00:03:40,810
Hello?

13
00:03:40,810 --> 00:03:41,510
Hello?

14
00:03:51,780 --> 00:03:53,860
Um, I was wondering if--

15
00:03:53,860 --> 00:03:54,610
oh, I'm sorry.

16
00:03:54,610 --> 00:03:56,680
Do you speak English?

17
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:57,820
Yes.

18
00:03:57,820 --> 00:04:01,000
Yes, well, I'm looking
 for my Uncle, Peter Kranek.

19
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:02,140
He was supposed to meet me here.

20
00:04:02,140 --> 00:04:03,400
Um, he lives right over--

21
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:04,790
I know him.

22
00:04:04,790 --> 00:04:06,060
Yes, well, he was
 supposed to come--

23
00:04:06,060 --> 00:04:08,000
We all know him.

24
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:09,730
Well, I was wondering
 if I could call

25
00:04:09,730 --> 00:04:11,860
him, if you have a telephone.

26
00:04:11,860 --> 00:04:13,360
No.

27
00:04:13,360 --> 00:04:14,750
No?

28
00:04:14,750 --> 00:04:18,460
Um, isn't that a
 phone right there?

29
00:04:18,460 --> 00:04:21,430
Oh, yes, we have a telephone.

30
00:04:21,430 --> 00:04:23,170
He does not.

31
00:04:23,170 --> 00:04:26,110
Well, can I call for a cab?

32
00:04:26,110 --> 00:04:27,190
WORKER: No.

33
00:04:27,190 --> 00:04:28,930
No, I can't call for a cab?

34
00:04:28,930 --> 00:04:31,640
No, there's no cab to call.

35
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:34,600
Well, can I at least
 walk there from here?

36
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:35,840
Yes.

37
00:04:35,840 --> 00:04:37,110
Will you show me?

38
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:40,180
Yes.

39
00:04:58,250 --> 00:04:59,660
Go down this road.

40
00:04:59,660 --> 00:05:01,130
Take the left fork.

41
00:05:01,130 --> 00:05:02,960
Walk for about five miles.

42
00:05:02,960 --> 00:05:04,070
You'll see a hill.

43
00:05:04,070 --> 00:05:05,690
On the hill, a big house--

44
00:05:05,690 --> 00:05:06,990
that is his.

45
00:05:06,990 --> 00:05:08,200
Thank you.

46
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:09,980
No, there's another way.

47
00:05:09,980 --> 00:05:11,160
Yes?

48
00:05:11,160 --> 00:05:13,370
Across the platform,
 the next train

49
00:05:13,370 --> 00:05:15,900
will come in about an hour.

50
00:05:15,900 --> 00:05:20,790
Take it and go back to
 wherever you came from.

51
00:05:20,790 --> 00:05:23,030
What?

52
00:05:23,030 --> 00:05:25,880
Thanks a lot, for nothing.

53
00:05:29,350 --> 00:05:33,800
[MUSIC PLAYING]

54
00:06:03,010 --> 00:06:07,460
[CHATTER]

55
00:06:09,440 --> 00:06:10,650
I don't know.

56
00:06:10,650 --> 00:06:11,420
Who's this going to be?

57
00:06:11,420 --> 00:06:12,180
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

58
00:06:12,180 --> 00:06:13,710
Go somewhere and do
 something about it, man.

59
00:06:17,060 --> 00:06:19,840
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

60
00:06:19,840 --> 00:06:20,990
Hey, [NON-ENGLISH].

61
00:06:24,380 --> 00:06:25,390
Don't be afraid.

62
00:06:25,390 --> 00:06:27,120
We won't hurt you.

63
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:28,360
I'm not afraid of you.

64
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:30,500
Then why do you
 stand so far away?

65
00:06:30,500 --> 00:06:32,350
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

66
00:06:32,350 --> 00:06:33,890
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

67
00:06:33,890 --> 00:06:35,990
OLD WOMAN: [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

68
00:06:35,990 --> 00:06:39,840
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]
 You know about him?

69
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:44,330
If this is Peter Kranek's
 house, he's my uncle.

70
00:06:44,330 --> 00:06:45,110
Why?

71
00:06:45,110 --> 00:06:46,400
Would you give
 him this from us?

72
00:06:46,400 --> 00:06:48,320
Why don't you just
 give it to him yourself?

73
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:49,790
I don't think he
 will take it from us,

74
00:06:49,790 --> 00:06:51,050
because we are Gypsies.

75
00:06:51,050 --> 00:06:52,520
Nobody likes us.

76
00:06:52,520 --> 00:06:54,140
Why don't you come over
 here and give it to me

77
00:06:54,140 --> 00:06:56,680
yourself if you want
 me to do you a favor?

78
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:57,870
Or are you afraid?

79
00:07:01,400 --> 00:07:03,680
Afraid of you?

80
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:05,150
No, not of you.

81
00:07:34,530 --> 00:07:38,520
[MUSIC PLAYING]

82
00:08:15,080 --> 00:08:16,570
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

83
00:08:22,530 --> 00:08:25,000
Why can't you people
 leave me in peace?

84
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:26,770
[GASPS]

85
00:08:26,770 --> 00:08:28,920
Eleanor?

86
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:30,380
What the hell are
 you doing here?

87
00:08:30,380 --> 00:08:31,930
I wrote your father
 not to send you.

88
00:08:31,930 --> 00:08:34,060
I-- I'm sorry.

89
00:08:34,060 --> 00:08:37,160
The letter must have
 gotten lost in the mail.

90
00:08:37,160 --> 00:08:42,420
Um, speaking of mail, someone
 gave me this to give to you.

91
00:08:42,420 --> 00:08:43,710
What is it?

92
00:08:43,710 --> 00:08:44,640
ELEANOR CRANE: I don't know.

93
00:08:44,640 --> 00:08:45,900
Who gave it to you?

94
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:47,730
There's this boy
 and this old woman

95
00:08:47,730 --> 00:08:49,070
down the hill in this car.

96
00:08:52,370 --> 00:08:53,070
Gypsies.

97
00:09:32,950 --> 00:09:34,750
I'm sorry.

98
00:09:34,750 --> 00:09:36,220
I know I told your
 parents you could

99
00:09:36,220 --> 00:09:37,810
stay here while they
 were at the conference,

100
00:09:37,810 --> 00:09:40,270
but it's not possible.

101
00:09:40,270 --> 00:09:42,280
You will have to
 go back to them.

102
00:09:42,280 --> 00:09:43,870
Why?

103
00:09:43,870 --> 00:09:44,750
I told you.

104
00:09:44,750 --> 00:09:45,840
It's--

105
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:48,100
No, why isn't it possible?

106
00:09:48,100 --> 00:09:49,700
There are reasons.

107
00:09:49,700 --> 00:09:51,420
Well, what are they?

108
00:09:51,420 --> 00:09:54,740
Look, Uncle Peter, normally
 I would be more polite.

109
00:09:54,740 --> 00:09:56,170
But around here,
 nobody feels like they

110
00:09:56,170 --> 00:09:57,940
need to be polite to me.

111
00:09:57,940 --> 00:10:00,160
So I figure, why bother?

112
00:10:00,160 --> 00:10:02,410
You talk like your
 father, sarcastic.

113
00:10:02,410 --> 00:10:03,940
It's not good for a girl.

114
00:10:03,940 --> 00:10:05,950
Yeah, well, if I asked
 in a more girlish way,

115
00:10:05,950 --> 00:10:07,780
would you answer me?

116
00:10:07,780 --> 00:10:09,700
PETER KRANEK: It's not safe.

117
00:10:09,700 --> 00:10:14,050
There have been murders here
 recently, terrible murders.

118
00:10:14,050 --> 00:10:16,360
Uncle Peter, I grew
 up in New York City.

119
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:17,720
It's different.

120
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:19,300
I-- I don't want you here.

121
00:10:19,300 --> 00:10:21,250
I cannot be responsible for you.

122
00:10:21,250 --> 00:10:23,520
I am not asking you to
 be responsible for me.

123
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:28,290
Yes, but my brother is asking
 me to be responsible for you.

124
00:10:28,290 --> 00:10:29,420
And I cannot.

125
00:10:29,420 --> 00:10:30,850
So you must go back to him.

126
00:10:33,820 --> 00:10:35,510
Come.

127
00:10:35,510 --> 00:10:37,130
We're going to the town.

128
00:10:37,130 --> 00:10:38,710
We'll call your
 father from there.

129
00:10:38,710 --> 00:10:40,290
You will leave today.

130
00:10:40,290 --> 00:10:42,260
Nice of you to have me.

131
00:10:42,260 --> 00:10:45,440
If I did not care about you,
 I would not care if you stayed.

132
00:10:45,440 --> 00:10:47,930
Well, let's just hope you
 care enough to carry my bags.

133
00:10:47,930 --> 00:10:50,240
I had to lug them
 all the way out here.

134
00:10:50,240 --> 00:10:51,200
Don't worry.

135
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:52,200
I have no telephone.

136
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:54,000
But I do have an automobile.

137
00:10:59,730 --> 00:11:01,000
Yes, I understand.

138
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:02,880
Yes, they are on the
 conference floor.

139
00:11:02,880 --> 00:11:04,840
But I'm in a train station
 with their daughter.

140
00:11:04,840 --> 00:11:06,850
Should I just leave her here?

141
00:11:06,850 --> 00:11:08,880
No, I cannot call
 back this evening.

142
00:11:08,880 --> 00:11:10,530
That is too late.

143
00:11:10,530 --> 00:11:12,480
You must-- [SIGHS].

144
00:11:12,480 --> 00:11:14,850
She must leave.

145
00:11:14,850 --> 00:11:15,690
Yes, I understand.

146
00:11:15,690 --> 00:11:18,120
You are a functionary, and
 you are incapable of making

147
00:11:18,120 --> 00:11:19,880
any decision at all.
 Goodbye.

148
00:11:23,950 --> 00:11:26,680
Your parents are on
 the conference floor.

149
00:11:26,680 --> 00:11:29,260
They cannot be disturbed
 by private calls.

150
00:11:29,260 --> 00:11:31,120
So you see this
 diplomatic business,

151
00:11:31,120 --> 00:11:34,660
it's very important, more
 important than family.

152
00:11:34,660 --> 00:11:37,390
- I guess.
 - It doesn't matter.

153
00:11:37,390 --> 00:11:39,340
You will go back this afternoon.

154
00:11:39,340 --> 00:11:40,600
WORKER: No.

155
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:42,120
What?

156
00:11:42,120 --> 00:11:43,980
No more trains
 till tomorrow noon.

157
00:11:43,980 --> 00:11:46,090
Then we will find a place
 for you to stay in town.

158
00:11:46,090 --> 00:11:47,410
Why in town?

159
00:11:47,410 --> 00:11:48,640
Yes, Mr. Kranek.

160
00:11:48,640 --> 00:11:49,390
Why in town?

161
00:11:49,390 --> 00:11:51,140
Surely you have
 enough room for us

162
00:11:51,140 --> 00:11:52,600
since you dismissed
 all your servants.

163
00:11:52,600 --> 00:11:53,350
I'm not-- I--

164
00:11:53,350 --> 00:11:57,370
Besides, sir, you know
 that the inn has been closed

165
00:11:57,370 --> 00:11:58,720
since poor Soren was killed.

166
00:12:01,600 --> 00:12:03,190
Look, if I'm going
 to be a burden,

167
00:12:03,190 --> 00:12:04,790
I can just stay
 here at the station.

168
00:12:04,790 --> 00:12:06,400
BOTH: No.

169
00:12:06,400 --> 00:12:08,480
You can come
 home with me, girl.

170
00:12:08,480 --> 00:12:09,180
You'll be safe.

171
00:12:09,180 --> 00:12:11,230
No, there is no reason
 why she should not

172
00:12:11,230 --> 00:12:13,330
stay at the mansion, no reason.

173
00:12:13,330 --> 00:12:16,300
Well then, perhaps
 you should be going.

174
00:12:16,300 --> 00:12:18,250
It's getting late.

175
00:12:18,250 --> 00:12:21,630
The sun will soon be
 down, and the full moon--

176
00:12:21,630 --> 00:12:22,570
That's enough.

177
00:12:22,570 --> 00:12:24,040
I know what you think.

178
00:12:24,040 --> 00:12:25,320
I know what you all think.

179
00:12:25,320 --> 00:12:27,310
And what is that, Mr. Kranek?

180
00:12:27,310 --> 00:12:29,080
Come along.

181
00:12:29,080 --> 00:12:29,880
Tomorrow you'll go.

182
00:12:42,340 --> 00:12:44,290
Listen to me very carefully.

183
00:12:44,290 --> 00:12:46,960
You must not attempt to
 leave this room tonight

184
00:12:46,960 --> 00:12:48,480
no matter what you may hear.

185
00:12:48,480 --> 00:12:49,930
And you may hear nothing.

186
00:12:49,930 --> 00:12:54,740
But no matter what happens,
 you must not leave this room.

187
00:12:54,740 --> 00:12:55,560
What is going on?

188
00:12:58,080 --> 00:12:59,460
I wish to God I knew.

189
00:12:59,460 --> 00:13:02,580
Please, please,
 stay in this room.

190
00:13:07,490 --> 00:13:08,960
[CLATTER]

191
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:10,440
Uncle Peter,
 what are you doing?

192
00:13:10,440 --> 00:13:11,420
You can't lock me in here.

193
00:13:11,420 --> 00:13:12,220
PETER KRANEK: I'm sorry.

194
00:13:12,220 --> 00:13:14,400
It's for your own protection.

195
00:13:14,400 --> 00:13:15,400
Uncle Peter, get back here.

196
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:16,390
What if there's a fire?

197
00:13:22,360 --> 00:13:26,330
[MUSIC PLAYING]

198
00:14:04,600 --> 00:14:08,580
[CLOCK CHIMES]

199
00:14:15,540 --> 00:14:17,560
A nice well-balanced supper.

200
00:14:34,990 --> 00:14:39,470
[MOANS]

201
00:14:48,430 --> 00:14:52,420
[WAILING]

202
00:14:56,700 --> 00:15:00,390
- Uncle Peter?
 - [GROWLS]

203
00:15:04,870 --> 00:15:07,360
[WAILING]

204
00:15:21,300 --> 00:15:23,790
[MOANS]

205
00:16:41,370 --> 00:16:43,840
"No steel shall stay.

206
00:16:43,840 --> 00:16:47,060
No door shall bar
 when the full moon

207
00:16:47,060 --> 00:16:50,390
shows the mark of the star.

208
00:16:50,390 --> 00:16:52,130
No prayers save.

209
00:16:52,130 --> 00:16:58,490
No curses reprieve a cursed
 death and men to grieve.

210
00:16:58,490 --> 00:17:01,290
To silver only since
 the world began

211
00:17:01,290 --> 00:17:05,680
can slay the wolf that
 walks like a man."

212
00:17:08,680 --> 00:17:12,670
[ROARING]

213
00:17:12,670 --> 00:17:15,660
[CHATTER]

214
00:17:24,150 --> 00:17:28,140
[SHOUTS IN DISTANCE]

215
00:17:28,140 --> 00:17:30,130
Take it in.

216
00:17:30,130 --> 00:17:31,130
[INAUDIBLE] wolf?

217
00:17:31,130 --> 00:17:34,630
[INAUDIBLE]?

218
00:17:34,630 --> 00:17:36,620
Get him, boy.
 Get him.

219
00:17:36,620 --> 00:17:38,120
[INAUDIBLE]

220
00:17:38,120 --> 00:17:43,110
[SHOUTING]

221
00:17:43,110 --> 00:17:44,610
[DOG BARKING]

222
00:17:44,610 --> 00:17:48,100
[INAUDIBLE]

223
00:17:58,080 --> 00:18:02,570
[DOG BARKING]

224
00:18:02,570 --> 00:18:03,570
[SNARLING]

225
00:18:03,570 --> 00:18:05,060
Ah!

226
00:18:05,060 --> 00:18:08,560
[MUSIC PLAYING]

227
00:18:08,560 --> 00:18:11,550
[ROARING]

228
00:18:15,540 --> 00:18:17,540
[MUFFLED SCREAMS]

229
00:18:25,820 --> 00:18:26,520
[CRIES]

230
00:18:30,010 --> 00:18:31,010
[GUN SHOT]

231
00:18:31,010 --> 00:18:32,510
[GUN SHOT]

232
00:18:32,510 --> 00:18:40,490
[GUN SHOT]
 - That way.

233
00:18:47,480 --> 00:18:50,970
[MUSIC PLAYING]

234
00:19:00,450 --> 00:19:04,450
[MUFFLED SHOUTING]

235
00:19:32,330 --> 00:19:33,820
[DOOR CLATTERS]

236
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:41,760
[DOOR SLAM]

237
00:19:41,760 --> 00:19:46,720
[FOOTSTEPS IN DISTANCE]

238
00:19:59,120 --> 00:20:00,110
[GROANS]

239
00:20:00,110 --> 00:20:01,650
Oh, my god.

240
00:20:01,650 --> 00:20:02,960
Oh, my god, Uncle Peter.

241
00:20:08,390 --> 00:20:09,380
Oh, my god.

242
00:20:36,550 --> 00:20:38,150
Are you OK?

243
00:20:38,150 --> 00:20:40,420
What happened to you?

244
00:20:40,420 --> 00:20:43,460
Peter, what happened?

245
00:20:43,460 --> 00:20:46,100
I don't know.

246
00:20:46,100 --> 00:20:47,940
I can't remember.

247
00:20:47,940 --> 00:20:53,930
Oh, god, I don't believe
 in Vukodlak superstitions.

248
00:20:53,930 --> 00:20:55,610
I'm raised not to believe.

249
00:20:58,800 --> 00:21:01,550
But now I believe.

250
00:21:01,550 --> 00:21:03,640
God help me, I believe.

251
00:21:03,640 --> 00:21:05,690
What are you talking about?

252
00:21:05,690 --> 00:21:10,850
Three months ago, I
 was sitting at that desk.

253
00:21:10,850 --> 00:21:12,020
The window was open.

254
00:21:21,810 --> 00:21:25,770
[MUSIC PLAYING]

255
00:21:28,240 --> 00:21:32,210
[GROWLING]

256
00:22:02,400 --> 00:22:07,730
I made myself believe
 that it hadn't been a wolf,

257
00:22:07,730 --> 00:22:11,240
that I hadn't seen what I saw.

258
00:22:11,240 --> 00:22:13,440
What was it?

259
00:22:13,440 --> 00:22:18,830
Vukodlak, the wolf
 that walks like a man.

260
00:22:18,830 --> 00:22:21,550
A werewolf.

261
00:22:21,550 --> 00:22:25,240
You're telling me you were
 attacked by a werewolf.

262
00:22:25,240 --> 00:22:31,280
The next night, the next night
 when the full moon rose, I--

263
00:22:31,280 --> 00:22:33,590
I blacked out.

264
00:22:33,590 --> 00:22:35,320
The next morning,
 my servants told me

265
00:22:35,320 --> 00:22:38,980
that I had vanished
 from my rooms,

266
00:22:38,980 --> 00:22:40,820
gone out the window
 from the second story

267
00:22:40,820 --> 00:22:41,860
and come back in the same way.

268
00:22:41,860 --> 00:22:44,050
But I didn't remember.

269
00:22:46,690 --> 00:22:52,370
Then they found the
 first body, Anna Skornik,

270
00:22:52,370 --> 00:22:56,460
torn as if by a wild animal.

271
00:22:56,460 --> 00:22:57,380
I didn't want to.

272
00:22:57,380 --> 00:22:58,670
Believe me.

273
00:22:58,670 --> 00:23:03,200
My mind did not want to
 know, but my heart knew.

274
00:23:03,200 --> 00:23:05,980
That is why I
 dismissed the servants.

275
00:23:05,980 --> 00:23:09,500
Though I tell myself it's
 because I did not want

276
00:23:09,500 --> 00:23:13,040
them harmed, but that is a lie.

277
00:23:13,040 --> 00:23:16,550
I dismissed them so
 that they would not see,

278
00:23:16,550 --> 00:23:18,500
so that they would
 not see what happened

279
00:23:18,500 --> 00:23:21,740
during the hours of the
 full moon, the hours

280
00:23:21,740 --> 00:23:24,110
that I can not remember.

281
00:23:24,110 --> 00:23:28,840
When I hunt in the night,
 when I kill in the night--

282
00:23:28,840 --> 00:23:32,030
A handy confession,
 Mr. Kranek.

283
00:23:32,030 --> 00:23:33,380
Ah.

284
00:23:33,380 --> 00:23:36,530
So you no longer call
 me by my first name.

285
00:23:36,530 --> 00:23:38,980
Or should I say, Inspector Krol.

286
00:23:38,980 --> 00:23:41,870
I have made a terrible
 mistake, Mr. Kranek.

287
00:23:41,870 --> 00:23:45,740
I refused to believe that a man
 like you could be a murderer.

288
00:23:45,740 --> 00:23:49,250
But now we follow a trail
 of blood to your door

289
00:23:49,250 --> 00:23:50,570
and hear your own confession.

290
00:23:50,570 --> 00:23:53,950
It's not his fault. He can't
 help what happened to him.

291
00:23:53,950 --> 00:23:55,510
Place Mr. Kranek under arrest.

292
00:23:58,580 --> 00:24:00,220
Wait.

293
00:24:00,220 --> 00:24:04,190
I strongly advise that
 you offer no resistance.

294
00:24:04,190 --> 00:24:06,040
Wait, you don't understand.

295
00:24:06,040 --> 00:24:07,320
The moon is full again tonight.

296
00:24:07,320 --> 00:24:09,970
You think that
 bullets will stop me?

297
00:24:09,970 --> 00:24:14,440
Oh, yes, Mr. Kranek,
 most assuredly so.

298
00:24:14,440 --> 00:24:17,560
They tell stories
 of wolves who walk,

299
00:24:17,560 --> 00:24:20,830
who are immune to bullets.

300
00:24:20,830 --> 00:24:24,470
But we know
 differently, don't we?

301
00:24:24,470 --> 00:24:27,960
The only monsters I have
 ever met, Mr. Kranek,

302
00:24:27,960 --> 00:24:30,470
are human monsters.

303
00:24:30,470 --> 00:24:32,080
And you are one.

304
00:24:32,080 --> 00:24:35,180
Bars will hold you.

305
00:24:35,180 --> 00:24:37,350
Bullets will kill you.

306
00:24:37,350 --> 00:24:39,090
And a rope will hang you.

307
00:24:42,260 --> 00:24:43,010
Take him away.

308
00:24:49,370 --> 00:24:53,010
You are very fortunate
 to be alive, young lady.

309
00:24:53,010 --> 00:24:55,570
I saw bullet
 holes in his chest.

310
00:24:55,570 --> 00:24:56,340
I saw them close up.

311
00:24:56,340 --> 00:24:57,580
I saw them disappear,
 just like--

312
00:24:57,580 --> 00:25:01,280
Just like on
 television, perhaps.

313
00:25:01,280 --> 00:25:02,690
Come along.

314
00:25:02,690 --> 00:25:04,780
We will discuss this
 further in town.

315
00:25:04,780 --> 00:25:06,760
Am I under arrest?

316
00:25:06,760 --> 00:25:09,090
Well, if you insist.

317
00:25:09,090 --> 00:25:13,080
I prefer to think that you are
 aiding us in our investigation.

318
00:25:13,080 --> 00:25:13,780
Come.

319
00:25:34,570 --> 00:25:35,560
OK, drop it.

320
00:25:44,970 --> 00:25:45,960
Sorry, I left them waiting.

321
00:25:45,960 --> 00:25:49,460
[INAUDIBLE]

322
00:25:49,460 --> 00:25:51,750
Listen to me.

323
00:25:51,750 --> 00:25:53,340
You have to understand.

324
00:25:53,340 --> 00:25:56,390
You will all die.
 - You first.

325
00:26:00,360 --> 00:26:04,000
No, listen to me.

326
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:06,090
You'll all die.

327
00:26:06,090 --> 00:26:07,080
Listen to me.

328
00:26:07,080 --> 00:26:11,050
[MUSIC PLAYING]

329
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:23,230
You didn't find any
 wounds on him, did you?

330
00:26:23,230 --> 00:26:26,990
No, only the scar
 on his shoulder.

331
00:26:26,990 --> 00:26:28,950
But you didn't find
 any blood on him.

332
00:26:28,950 --> 00:26:32,140
No, but he could have cleaned
 it off after he reached home.

333
00:26:32,140 --> 00:26:34,170
But he didn't.

334
00:26:34,170 --> 00:26:35,600
Look, I was there.

335
00:26:35,600 --> 00:26:37,300
I-- I saw the bullet
 holes, and I--

336
00:26:37,300 --> 00:26:39,260
I saw--
 - Yes, I know.

337
00:26:39,260 --> 00:26:41,630
The, uh, bullet holes closed up.

338
00:26:41,630 --> 00:26:45,200
Please forgive me for saying
 this, Ms. Crane, but, uh,

339
00:26:45,200 --> 00:26:48,500
to my mind, it is much more
 likely that young girls lie

340
00:26:48,500 --> 00:26:52,030
than that men turn into wolves.

341
00:26:52,030 --> 00:26:54,910
You helped him clean off
 the blood, didn't you?

342
00:26:54,910 --> 00:26:55,860
No.

343
00:26:55,860 --> 00:26:57,710
And I'm not lying to you.

344
00:26:57,710 --> 00:27:02,940
Well, I talked to
 your father in Geneva.

345
00:27:02,940 --> 00:27:05,940
And you will return to
 him by tomorrow's train.

346
00:27:05,940 --> 00:27:08,090
What's going to
 happen to Peter?

347
00:27:08,090 --> 00:27:11,890
That is for the
 court to decide,

348
00:27:11,890 --> 00:27:17,070
perhaps the madhouse,
 perhaps death by hanging.

349
00:27:17,070 --> 00:27:18,920
I'm sorry, Ms. Crane.

350
00:27:18,920 --> 00:27:20,530
I know this must be
 very upsetting to you,

351
00:27:20,530 --> 00:27:24,400
but, uh, I don't think you
 would want me to lie to you.

352
00:27:24,400 --> 00:27:25,210
Listen, Mister--

353
00:27:25,210 --> 00:27:27,600
Inspector.

354
00:27:27,600 --> 00:27:33,410
Inspector, tonight when the
 full moon rises, my uncle's

355
00:27:33,410 --> 00:27:34,570
going to change.

356
00:27:34,570 --> 00:27:36,500
Look, he's going to become--

357
00:27:36,500 --> 00:27:39,440
Ah, that is something I
 would like very much to see.

358
00:27:39,440 --> 00:27:41,450
Am I free to go?

359
00:27:41,450 --> 00:27:43,360
Yes, of course.

360
00:27:43,360 --> 00:27:48,340
My constable can drive to
 your uncle's residence.

361
00:27:48,340 --> 00:27:49,740
I'll walk.

362
00:27:49,740 --> 00:27:50,470
As you wish.

363
00:27:50,470 --> 00:27:51,610
The region is quite safe.

364
00:27:51,610 --> 00:27:54,070
You will not be troubled, now.

365
00:28:28,190 --> 00:28:31,010
Aren't you a bit
 young to be driving?

366
00:28:31,010 --> 00:28:32,890
My grandmother
 wants to see you.

367
00:28:32,890 --> 00:28:33,710
Get in.

368
00:28:33,710 --> 00:28:34,490
Is that an order?

369
00:28:34,490 --> 00:28:36,120
How can I give you an order?

370
00:28:36,120 --> 00:28:37,820
You're not my sister.
 Get in.

371
00:29:14,620 --> 00:29:16,760
You like it?

372
00:29:16,760 --> 00:29:20,250
Good, huh?

373
00:29:20,250 --> 00:29:22,400
Yes, and thank you.

374
00:29:22,400 --> 00:29:24,320
You're welcome.
 See?

375
00:29:24,320 --> 00:29:26,640
I'm polite.

376
00:29:26,640 --> 00:29:27,380
Now come.

377
00:29:27,380 --> 00:29:30,230
My grandmother wants to see you.

378
00:29:30,230 --> 00:29:31,610
Isn't she here?

379
00:29:31,610 --> 00:29:32,930
No, close.

380
00:29:32,930 --> 00:29:36,750
She wants to talk privately.
 Let's go.

381
00:29:36,750 --> 00:29:37,450
Come on.

382
00:29:45,400 --> 00:29:48,070
Where are we going?

383
00:29:48,070 --> 00:29:48,920
We're really close.

384
00:29:48,920 --> 00:29:49,620
It's close.

385
00:29:52,500 --> 00:29:53,940
Here.

