00:30:22,140 --> 00:30:25,840
You know what he is, about
 the curse of the wolf.

390
00:30:25,840 --> 00:30:28,550
He took it from my
 grandmother's brother.

391
00:30:28,550 --> 00:30:30,530
He had it for a long time.

392
00:30:30,530 --> 00:30:32,420
Most time, when
 the full is full,

393
00:30:32,420 --> 00:30:35,210
they keep him chained,
 give him animals to kill.

394
00:30:35,210 --> 00:30:37,630
Sometimes he'd get
 loose, kill men.

395
00:30:37,630 --> 00:30:39,880
You understand?

396
00:30:39,880 --> 00:30:42,380
So he's the one who
 attacked my uncle.

397
00:30:42,380 --> 00:30:45,790
Yes, your uncle stabbed
 him with a silver blade,

398
00:30:45,790 --> 00:30:46,780
killed him.

399
00:30:46,780 --> 00:30:48,110
He is buried here.

400
00:30:48,110 --> 00:30:52,490
Now, your uncle, he
 can't lose the curse.

401
00:30:52,490 --> 00:30:53,800
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

402
00:30:53,800 --> 00:30:56,710
She says nothing
