00:31:19,030 --> 00:31:20,330
CARL: You know how?

412
00:31:20,330 --> 00:31:25,710
Pull back hammer till
 it clicks like this.

413
00:31:25,710 --> 00:31:26,790
Then shoot.
 - Wait.

414
00:31:26,790 --> 00:31:28,090
Hold on.
 Wait a second.

415
00:31:28,090 --> 00:31:31,550
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

416
00:31:31,550 --> 00:31:33,250
These are silver.

417
00:31:33,250 --> 00:31:35,900
We made them from the
 blade that killed my uncle,

418
00:31:35,900 --> 00:31:37,420
only enough for three.

419
00:31:37,420 --> 00:31:39,950
Are you trying to tell me
 she wants me to kill my uncle?

420
00:31:39,950 --> 00:31:42,070
Take it.

421
00:31:42,070 --> 00:31:43,820
No, I don't want it.

422
00:31:43,820 --> 00:31:46,090
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

423
00:31:48,790 --> 00:31:51,330
Take for your uncle.

424
00:31:51,330 --> 00:31:54,380
[INAUDIBLE] his death.

425
00:31:54,380 --> 00:31:56,150
Take.

426
00:31:56,150 --> 00:31:58,530
But he is your
 uncle, of course.

427
00:31:58,530 --> 00:31:59,230
Come.

428
00:32:13,870 --> 00:32:15,260
Take me back to the village.

429
00:32:15,260 --> 00:32:17,050
Where in the village?

430
00:32:17,050 --> 00:32:18,730
- The police station.
 - OK.

431
00:32:18,730 --> 00:32:19,910
I'll take you.

432
00:32:33,380 --> 00:32:36,400
- I have to see him now.
 - Please.

433
00:32:36,400 --> 00:32:38,190
I want to see my uncle.

434
00:32:40,410 --> 00:32:41,110
Why?

435
00:32:44,860 --> 00:32:46,400
Does it matter why?

436
00:32:46,400 --> 00:32:49,700
Sometimes.

437
00:32:49,700 --> 00:32:54,280
You have told me that you are
 not very close to your uncle,

438
00:32:54,280 --> 00:32:57,270
that you have not seen
 him since you were a baby.

439
00:32:57,270 --> 00:33:01,170
You have only seen him for a
 few minutes since you came here.

440
00:33:01,170 --> 00:33:03,390
And even during
 that time, he tried

441
00:33:03,390 --> 00:33:07,350
to get you to go back to Geneva
 and locked you in a bedroom

442
00:33:07,350 --> 00:33:08,430
without food.

443
00:33:08,430 --> 00:33:12,240
So I wonder, what
 will you tell him?

444
00:33:12,240 --> 00:33:13,980
What will you ask him?

445
00:33:13,980 --> 00:33:16,770
Look, Inspector, I don't
 want to argue with you.

446
00:33:16,770 --> 00:33:17,790
Can I see him or not?

447
00:33:19,890 --> 00:33:20,590
Come along.

448
00:33:34,370 --> 00:33:38,540
So you've come to
 visit me after all.

449
00:33:38,540 --> 00:33:41,690
Or is it to be interrogation?

450
00:33:41,690 --> 00:33:43,950
You need all these
 men to guard my uncle.

451
00:33:43,950 --> 00:33:45,740
It is a reasonable precaution.

452
00:33:45,740 --> 00:33:48,230
It's an absurdity,
 and he knows it.

453
00:33:48,230 --> 00:33:51,320
Inspector, I'd like
 to see him alone.

454
00:33:51,320 --> 00:33:53,690
That is quite impossible.

455
00:33:53,690 --> 00:33:56,070
What do you think
 I'll do to her, huh?

456
00:33:56,070 --> 00:33:56,840
What are you afraid of?

457
00:34:00,470 --> 00:34:03,790
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

458
00:34:07,520 --> 00:34:10,070
I do not think he can
 harm you, Ms. Crane.

459
00:34:10,070 --> 00:34:11,910
But if you take my
 advice, you won't

460
00:34:11,910 --> 00:34:13,360
get too close to the bars.

461
00:34:21,640 --> 00:34:24,370
- Thank you for coming.
 - Uh, Peter, look--

462
00:34:24,370 --> 00:34:29,410
Please, I need you to take
 a message to your father.

463
00:34:29,410 --> 00:34:34,370
For a long time, as boys,
 as young men, we were close.

464
00:34:34,370 --> 00:34:38,500
And then for a long time, we
 were not close, just because I

465
00:34:38,500 --> 00:34:41,110
was jealous of your father.

466
00:34:41,110 --> 00:34:42,260
I know this now.

467
00:34:42,260 --> 00:34:44,200
Because he was successful?

468
00:34:44,200 --> 00:34:47,170
No, because your
 father saw his future,

469
00:34:47,170 --> 00:34:52,130
saw his destiny and-- and
 pursued it and achieved it.

470
00:34:52,130 --> 00:34:54,600
And I could not.

471
00:34:54,600 --> 00:34:57,300
I never saw my destiny.

472
00:34:57,300 --> 00:34:58,640
Now it is too late for anything.

473
00:35:02,510 --> 00:35:06,130
Please tell him that I'm sorry.
 - I will.

474
00:35:08,880 --> 00:35:12,260
Look, Peter, is there any--
 anything I can do for you?

475
00:35:12,260 --> 00:35:14,560
What needs to be done
 I'm afraid you cannot do.

476
00:35:24,990 --> 00:35:26,980
I'm sorry.

477
00:35:26,980 --> 00:35:30,460
I am so sorry.

478
00:35:30,460 --> 00:35:31,950
What?

479
00:35:31,950 --> 00:35:32,950
I can't do it.

480
00:35:32,950 --> 00:35:33,940
I can't do this.

481
00:35:33,940 --> 00:35:35,970
I can't do it.

482
00:35:35,970 --> 00:35:38,840
Eleanor?

483
00:35:38,840 --> 00:35:39,830
Ms. Crane?

484
00:35:45,760 --> 00:35:50,200
[CRYING]

485
00:35:51,480 --> 00:35:52,180
CARL: Hey.

486
00:35:59,600 --> 00:36:01,120
I didn't hear any shots.

487
00:36:01,120 --> 00:36:04,780
I don't see any
 policemen running.

488
00:36:04,780 --> 00:36:06,620
Don't feel bad.
 We couldn't do it either.

489
00:36:06,620 --> 00:36:07,320
Come on.

490
00:36:07,320 --> 00:36:08,520
I'll take you to
 your uncle's house.

491
00:36:14,410 --> 00:36:18,900
[MUSIC PLAYING]

492
00:36:30,890 --> 00:36:34,250
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

493
00:36:44,740 --> 00:36:47,620
Please, I can't stop it.

494
00:36:47,620 --> 00:36:49,610
Run.
 Run.

495
00:36:53,110 --> 00:36:56,100
Run, run, run, run, run, run.

496
00:36:56,100 --> 00:37:00,090
[GROANING]

497
00:37:10,570 --> 00:37:14,560
[SNARLS]

498
00:37:20,050 --> 00:37:23,050
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

499
00:37:23,050 --> 00:37:25,540
[ROARS]

500
00:37:30,530 --> 00:37:32,030
[INAUDIBLE] I shot him.

501
00:37:54,980 --> 00:37:59,970
[ROARING]

502
00:37:59,970 --> 00:38:04,460
[MUSIC PLAYING]

503
00:38:16,940 --> 00:38:21,430
[ANIMAL SCREAMS IN DISTANCE]

504
00:38:55,360 --> 00:39:00,850
[HOWLS]

505
00:39:00,850 --> 00:39:04,840
[MUSIC PLAYING]

506
00:40:44,140 --> 00:40:46,640
Oh, no.
 Oh.

507
00:40:52,130 --> 00:40:53,130
[SCREAMS]

508
00:40:53,130 --> 00:40:54,620
[GROWLS]

509
00:41:04,590 --> 00:41:05,370
Please.

510
00:41:05,370 --> 00:41:06,720
It's me.

511
00:41:06,720 --> 00:41:07,690
It's Eleanor.

512
00:41:07,690 --> 00:41:09,550
Please don't make me
 shoot you, please.

513
00:41:09,550 --> 00:41:11,130
Please, Uncle Peter,
 these are silver bullets.

514
00:41:11,130 --> 00:41:13,110
Please don't make me kill you.

515
00:41:16,830 --> 00:41:17,530
It's me.

516
00:41:21,460 --> 00:41:22,940
Yeah, it's Eleanor.

517
00:41:22,940 --> 00:41:25,060
Yes, it's me.

518
00:41:25,060 --> 00:41:25,860
It's me.

519
00:41:25,860 --> 00:41:27,170
Please, Uncle Peter, it's me.

520
00:41:27,170 --> 00:41:28,050
Please remember.

521
00:41:28,050 --> 00:41:28,930
It's me.

522
00:41:28,930 --> 00:41:30,650
Please, it's me, Eleanor.
 Remember?

523
00:41:30,650 --> 00:41:33,250
It's me.

524
00:41:33,250 --> 00:41:34,230
[ROARS]

525
00:41:46,920 --> 00:41:49,370
Oh, ah.

